(28, 76, 'Bachelor of Science (Hons) Biochemistry', 'What will I learn?\r\n\r\nThe importance of biochemistry has grown as techniques for its study become more sophisticated with applications in genetic engineering and molecular bioengineering as well as in the physiological and medical areas. The topics of molecular biology, biotechnology and genetic engineering are derived from biochemistry and the subject interfaces with a wide range of other biology-related disciplines. Biochemistry is also the core subject in bioinformatics which links the biological sciences to computer technology.\r\n\r\nThe program aims to allow students to understand, analyze, practice and evaluate the knowledge and laboratory skills of a range of biochemistry topics. It provides strong training in practical methods, data analysis and problem solving related to biochemistry.\r\n\r\nHighlights\r\n\r\n    UTAR is the only private university in Malaysia offered Bachelor of Science (Hons) Biochemistry.\r\n    The program is accredited by MQA and recognized by Jabatan Perkhidmatan Awam (JPA).\r\n    60% of the biochemistry lecturers are PhD holders.\r\n\r\nCareer Prospects\r\n\r\n    Biochemist\r\n    Scientific Officer\r\n    Protein Chemist\r\n    Phylogenetic\r\n    Food Analyst\r\n    Laboratory Executive / Manager\r\n    Bioinformatics Software Developer\r\n\r\nIn which department am I?\r\nFaculty of Science\r\nStudy options\r\nFull Time (3 years)\r\nRegistration fees\r\nRM19,083.33 (US $ 4,687) per year\r\n\r\n* The price shown is indicative price, please contact with the university\r\nstarting date\r\n\r\n27 May 2019, 14 October 2019\r\nPlace of the session\r\n\r\nKampar Campus\r\n\r\nPerak,\r\n\r\nMalaysia\r\nAdmission requirements\r\nFor students from Egypt\r\nEntry with Standard Qualifications: UTAR welcomes applicants with any of the following qualifications for entry to Bachelor\'s Honors Degree Program: Sijil Tinggi Persekolahan Malaysia (STPM); Unified Examination Certificate (UEC); A-Levels; South Australian Maturation (SAM); Canadian Pre-University (CPU). Entry with Other Qualifications: Applicants with qualifications other than those described above, for example, a Diploma from a college / institution / polytechnic may also apply for admission to UTAR programs. English Language Requirements: International English Language Testing System (IELTS) -5.0; Paper-based TOEFL-410; Internet-based Testing (iBT) - new TOEFL - 34; SPM English Language / O-level English Language-Credit; MUET - Band 3; UEC English Language - Grade B; Common European Framework of Reference for Languages ??(CEFR) - B1.\r\nFor international students\r\n\r\nAny foreign qualification that is equivalent to below given Malaysian qualifications is eligible for admission to this program:\r\n\r\nSTPM with 2 principal passages of Grade C + or\r\n\r\nA-Level with 2 pass or\r\n\r\nSouth Australian Matriculation with an Australian Tertiary Admission Rank (ATAR) 70 and Grade B in 2 subjects Egypt\r\n\r\nCanadian Pre-University (CPU) with an average of 70% in 6 subjects\r\n\r\nOther equivalent qualifications recognized by the Malaysian Government and\r\n\r\nEntry requirements may vary from country to country.\r\n\r\nThey also must have the following minimum score are as follows:\r\n\r\nInternational English Language Testing System (IELTS): 5.0\r\n\r\nInternet-based Testing (IBT) - TOEFL: 34\r\n\r\nPaper-based TOEFL: 410\r\n\r\nCambridge English: Advance (CAE) 160\r\n\r\nCambridge English: Proficiency (CPE) 180\r\n\r\nPearson Test of English (PTE) 36\r\n\r\nMUET: Band 3\r\n\r\nCommon European Framework of Reference for Languages ??(CEFR): B1\r\n\r\nSome Bachelor \'degree programs may require higher English Language test scores as set by the Ministry of Higher Education (MOHE) or the Malaysian Qualificationsn Agency (MQA). These programs are:\r\n\r\nBusiness: IELTS 5.5 / TOEFL 550 / equivalent (IELTS 6.0 / equivalent for Finance)\r\n\r\nComputing / English Language / English Education: IELTS 6.0 / TOEFL 550 / equivalent\r\n\r\nBiomedical Science / Chinese Medicine / Journalism / Public Relations / Physiotherapy: IELTS 5.5 / TOEFL 550 / equivalent\r\n\r\nNursing: IELTS 5.5 / TOEFL 515 / equivalent\r\n\r\nM.B.B.S .: IELTS 6.5 / TOEFL 580 / equivalent'),
(28, 77, 'Foundation in Arts', 'What will I learn?\r\n\r\nThe UTAR Foundation Program is a full-time intensive program that has been designed to equip students with the necessary knowledge and skills for smooth transition into the undergraduate studies in UTAR.\r\n\r\nIt offers the shortest pathway for eligible students to progress into the undergraduate studies of their choice within one year. With the flexible program structure, students may complete their Foundation programs to their desired pace of up to two years.\r\n\r\nThere are various courses that will enhance students\' academic knowledge, expose students to the latest developments in the relative areas of studies and foster their critical thinking skills. Simultaneously, it also sharpens students\' presentation skills and English language proficiency.\r\n\r\nCore Subject\r\n\r\nAcademic English\r\n\r\nBasic English\r\n\r\nComputing Technology\r\n\r\nCritical Thinking\r\n\r\nManagement\r\n\r\nMarketing\r\nIn which department am I?\r\nCenter for Foundation Studies (Sungai Long Campus)\r\nStudy options\r\nFull Time (1 Year)\r\nRegistration fees\r\nRM16,650.00 (US $ 4,089) per year\r\n\r\n* The price shown is indicative price, please contact with the university\r\nstarting date\r\n\r\n27 May 2019, 14 October 2019\r\nPlace of the session\r\n\r\nUniversiti Tunku Abdul Rahman (UTAR)\r\n\r\nJalan Universiti Bandar Barat,\r\n\r\nKampar,\r\n\r\nPerak,\r\n\r\n31900, Malaysia\r\nAdmission requirements\r\nFor students from Egypt\r\nStudents must have pass SPM with 5 credits or Unifield Examination Certificate (UEC) with Grade B in 3 subjects or O-Level with 5 credits or other equivalent qualifications recognized by the Malaysian Government. English Language Requirements: They also must have the following minimum score as follows: International English Language Testing System (IELTS): 5.0; Internet-based Testing (IBT) - TOEFL: 59; Computer-based TOEFL: 170; Paper-based TOEFL: 500; MUET: Band 3.\r\nFor international students\r\n\r\nAny foreign qualification that is equivalent to below provided Malaysian qualifications is eligible for admission to this program: SPM with 5 credits OR Unifield Examination Certificate (UEC) with Grade B in 3 subjects OR O-Level with 5 credits OR Other equivalent qualifications recognized by the Malaysian Government.\r\n\r\nThey also must have the following minimum score are as follows:\r\n\r\nInternational English Language Testing System (IELTS): 4.0\r\n\r\nTOEFL IBT: 30\r\n\r\nTOEFL PBT: 397\r\n\r\nCambridge English: Advance (CAE) - 160\r\n\r\nCambridge English: (CPE) - 180\r\n\r\nPerson Test of English (PTE): 30\r\n\r\nMalaysia University English Test (MUET): Band 2\r\n\r\nCEFR: A2');
